project: Touch the Icon to Select what piece you want
Touch the block to Rotate 90 degrees clockwise
Touch the icon to flip 180 degrees on the x-axis, and to select a side of the game board
Touch the icon to create the desired block

One reversible paying board, with a different puzzle game on each side. Twenty-one black oblong pieces.
(RemoveDominos playing pieces from plastic runners by rotating each piece in place until free.)
To place all twenty-one pieces on the board so that the white tipped pegs go through the holes in the pieces.
Put pieces, one at a time, on the board.

Note that no two black pieces are alike, nut there is more than one place where a particular piece might fit on the board. Pieces can be placed on the board either vertically or horizontally. There is only one correct solution for each side of the board.
